shared_text:
Winthrop Harbor School District
March 13 at 1:05 PM ¬∑

Families,
We are living in a rapidly evolving time with changes on how to maintain a safe and orderly environment for all of our students, staff, and families in Winthrop Harbor. It is with a heavy heart that I have decided to cancel school all next week and use them as our back-up emergency days. This will take us to our scheduled spring break during the week of March 23rd. We anticipate this short break will allow for better planning and time to understand the effects of the spread of the Coronavirus (COVID-19). The building principals will be following up with a letter to parents explaining how students may continue to learn using their Chromebooks.
We will send out further updates when they become available. I apologize for any inconveniences this may cause families, but we must continue to make student safety a priority.
Thank you,
Jeffrey McCartney
Superintendent of Schools
Winthrop Harbor School District #1

post_text: The Sweetheart Dance is postponed. We are going to closely monitor the pandemic of COVID-19 (Coronavirus), but in consultation with the school administration and the advising being given by public health experts, it is in the best interest of everyone to avoid the risk of large gatherings at this time. As the situation evolves over the next few weeks, we hope to determine if we will be able to reschedule. We apologize for any inconvenience this causes and will do our best to keep you informed as new details come together.

We apologize for any inconvenience this causes and will do our best to keep you informed as new details come together.

post_text:
This year‚Äôs all-inclusive, nonexclusive Sweetheart Dance is still on as planned. You know what else is all-inclusive, and nonexclusive? COVID-19 (Coronavirus). We are monitoring and taking very seriously the concerns over COVID-19, especially as Lake County had their first case this week. While we want to forge ahead, we all play a role in helping to keep each other healthy. If you are sick, please stay home. If you have a compromised immune system, please stay home. There will not be reimbursements, but your health and the health of our community is more important. Continue to take preventive actions to prevent the spread of illness ‚Äì remember the 3 C‚Äôs ‚Äì clean, cover, contain.

We are looking forward to building sweet memories together Friday night!

If you missed the pre sale, that‚Äôs ok, you can still join us and pay at the door!
